{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, Zhang et al.",
    "conducted a longitudinal study by deploying IntelliCare, a suite of mental health apps that individuals can selectively use, to people with depression or anxiety [105].",
    "The study showed that offering a variety of intervention choices not only enhanced individuals' autonomy but also addressed their needs for encouragement, goal setting, and reflection across different situations [105].",
    "Among these existing support tools, chatbots have become increasingly prominent for their ability to engage individuals in natural language conversations, providing empathy and intimacy akin to human companions [1,29,48,85,90].",
    "More importantly, as an agent with humanlike attributes, chatbots can be customized through multiple aspects, such as communication style and visual appearance, which allows researchers to explore a broad range of customization opportunities [1,22,39,90,99]."
  ]
}